def: Having a suburb or suburbs on its outer part.
Similarly in arrangement of parts; -- the opposite ofheterotaxy.
Affected with amaurosis; having the characteristics ofamaurosis.
A medicine that strengthens the stomach and excites its action.
To change by alchemy; to transmute. Lovelace.
A stringed instrument of music resembling the lute or theviolin, but larger, and having six strings, three of silk coveredwith silver wire, and three of catgut, -- played upon with thefingers.

A process which consists in surrounding a solid body with thepowder of other substances, and heating the whole to a degree notsufficient to cause fusion, the physical properties of the body beingchanged by chemical combination with powder; thus iron becomes steelby cementation with charcoal, and green glass becomes porcelain bycementation with sand.
